  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 350&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Cut the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and slice the<strong>&nbsp;red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a very low heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> onion</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 20 min, until softened and caramelised&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile<strong>,</strong> add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of boiling water with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and&nbsp;return to the pot</p>\r\n<p>Place the <strong>sausages</strong> onto a lightly oiled baking tray and put them into the oven for an initial 10 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716...step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716...step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716...step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716...step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716...step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>beef</strong>&nbsp;<strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> boiled water, add the <strong>fig relish</strong> and mix until fully combined &ndash; this is your <strong>fig stock</strong></p>\r\n<p>Trim the <strong>green beans&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>chives</strong> finely&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut out a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> and place the <strong>green beans</strong> in the middle</p>\r\n<p>Scrunch&nbsp;up the edges of the foil slightly, then add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> and close the parcel tightly&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>sausages</strong> have had 10 min oven time, add&nbsp;the parcel to the tray and put it back into the oven for a further 15 min</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716...step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716...step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716...step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716...step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716...step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>onions</strong> have softened, increase the heat to medium and add the <strong>S</strong><strong><strong>haoxing</strong> wine&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 30 sec or until the Shaoxing wine has evaporated&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Stir 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong>&nbsp;into the onions until evenly coated, then add the <strong>fig stock</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 5 min or until the sauce has thickened to a gravy-like consistency</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the drained <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat and add 60ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml]</span><strong> milk</strong> and 40g <span class=\"text-danger\">[80g]</span><strong> butter</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mash until smooth, then add the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>cheese</strong> and stir through&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Remove the mash from the heat and stir through the <strong>chives</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/716.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
